# Authentication

The Clientela API uses tokens to authenticate requests. Your token carries many privileges, so **be sure to keep it secure!** Do not share it or expose it on publicly available areas such as GitHub or client-side code.

<br />

```shell
curl -X 'POST' 'https://clientela.admetricks.com/o/token/?username=YOUR_USERNAME&password=YOUR_PASSWORD&client_id=IW8M80h7qgCaSz4hPm3gr3wJP89NiJTPyhkwPurT&client_secret=KnBW84uyHlxwlNrKOXyym6Ro1IT6IlYdhScdop63hHddCzJIxUwDG7VItNgEONb1U2ebEH6fBmkYgX9LrZD4uqFJlYscHYn9MLxOm2qVccNE2WGEuePpKA7t3jQ2CvMu&grant_type=password'
```

```javascript
const credentials = {
  username: "YOUR_USERNAME",
  password: "YOUR_PASSWORD"
}

const client = {
  id: "IW8M80h7qgCaSz4hPm3gr3wJP89NiJTPyhkwPurT",
  secret: "KnBW84uyHlxwlNrKOXyym6Ro1IT6IlYdhScdop63hHddCzJIxUwDG7VItNgEONb1U2ebEH6fBmkYgX9LrZD4uqFJlYscHYn9MLxOm2qVccNE2WGEuePpKA7t3jQ2CvMu"
}

const endpoint = `https://clientela.admetricks.com/o/token/?username=${credentials.username}&password=${credentials.password}&client_id=${client.id}&client_secret=${client.secret}&grant_type=password`

fetch(endpoint, {
  body: null,
  method: "POST",
})
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(token => console.log(token)) // print your token data
```

